      "content": "### GET /user\n\nThe `GET /user` endpoint retrieves information about the authenticated user.\n\n#### Request Parameters\n\n*   `username`: The username of the user to retrieve information for. (Required)\n*   `fields`: A comma-separated list of fields to include in the response. (Optional, default: `id, name, email`)\n\n#### Response\n\nThe response will include the following fields:\n\n*   `id`: The unique identifier for the user.\n*   `name`: The user's full name.\n*   `email`: The user's email address.\n*   `created_at`: The timestamp when the user account was created.\n*   `last_login`: The timestamp of the user's last login.\n*   `role`: The user's role in the system.\n\n#### Security Considerations\n\n*   **Authentication**: This endpoint requires authentication to ensure that only authorized users can access their own information.\n*   **Authorization**: The user's role determines the level of access to system resources.\n*   **Data Encryption**: All user data is encrypted in transit using HTTPS.\n\n#### Error Codes\n\n| HTTP Status Code | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| 401 Unauthorized | Authentication failed. |\n| 403 Forbidden | User",
